This is sort of a mix between a bug and a feature request, but...

`SteppablePipeline.Begin` has a `void` return type even though `begin` blocks can emit pipeline output.  These means if you aren't passing an `EngineIntrinsics` or `InternalCommand` to `SteppablePipeline.Begin` any pipeline output is just swallowed.

## Proposed technical implementation details (optional)

```diff
namespace System.Management.Automation
{
    public sealed class SteppablePipeline : IDisposable
    {
+        public Array BeginWithOutput(bool expectingInput);
    }
}
```

(except probably with better name)

Or:


```diff
namespace System.Management.Automation
{
    public sealed class SteppablePipeline : IDisposable
    {
+        public void Begin(bool expectingInput, out Array output);
    }
}
```
